# Philosophy

These are collaboration guidelines, not coding rules.

## How to work on this project

- Prefer small, iterative changes over large rewrites.
- Avoid large refactors unless explicitly requested.
- Do not introduce new dependencies unless they provide clear, lasting value.
- Explain architectural decisions before making them when the choice is not obvious.
- Ask before expanding scope beyond what was requested.
- Match existing conventions — read surrounding code before writing new code.
- Minimize diff size; do not change unrelated code.
- Each change should leave the app runnable.
- Do not over-engineer abstractions for features that do not exist yet.
- Do not add tests, docs, or tooling unless requested or clearly needed.

## When uncertain

- Prefer the simpler approach.
- Say what you plan to do and why before a multi-file change.
- Flag trade-offs instead of silently choosing one path.

## Long-term mindset

This is a multi-year project. Favor maintainable structure over speed today.
